[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1804},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2025\u002F09\u002F23\u002Fday-23-php-huh-an-elephant\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2025\u002F09\u002F23\u002Fday-23-php-huh-an-elephant\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2025\u002F09\u002F23\u002Fday-23-php-huh-an-elephant\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2025\u002F09\u002F23\u002Fday-23-php-huh-an-elephant\u002F":1780,"related:\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2025\u002F09\u002F23\u002Fday-23-php-huh-an-elephant\u002F":1789},"\u002Flearnexp\u002F20250923\u002F2062222122\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1759,"date":1760,"description":1761,"extension":1762,"lang":1763,"meta":1764,"navigation":334,"path":1765,"readingMinutes":1766,"seo":1767,"standalone":1768,"stem":1769,"tags":1770,"tldr":1776,"updated":1777,"url":1778,"__hash__":1779},"content\u002Fen\u002FLearning\u002Fday-23-php-huh-an-elephant.md","【Day 23】PHP? Huh? An Elephant?","2062254212",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1753},"minimark",[11,28,35,39,42,45,48,56,59,62,65,68,71,78,81,84,87,90,93,136,146,149,152,155,442,445,448,451,454,457,460,463,466,469,475,479,482,485,1084,1091,1094,1097,1403,1406,1409,1630,1641,1647,1650,1653,1681,1684,1687,1690,1694,1697,1701,1704,1749],[12,13,16],"callout",{"title":14,"type":15},"Warning","warning",[17,18,19,20,27],"p",{},"This series has been rewritten and published as a book, currently available at ",[21,22,26],"a",{"href":23,"rel":24},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.tenlong.com.tw\u002Fproducts\u002F9786267889251?list_name=i-r-zh_tw",[25],"nofollow","Tenlong Bookstore"," (in Traditional Chinese). (Updated 2026\u002F05\u002F07)\nThe book version was essentially rewritten from scratch — I filled in the parts of the story I couldn't fully tell during the original IT Home serialization, and cleaned up sections where the writing wasn't precise enough. It's a version I'm much happier with.\nIf you enjoy this post and want more, or want the polished version, the book is the way to go. The blog and IT Home will keep the original serialized version for archive purposes — please treat the book as the authoritative reference.",[17,29,30],{},[31,32],"img",{"alt":33,"src":34},"PHP? Huh? An elephant?","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Flearnexp\u002Fithelp-2025\u002Fday23\u002FChatGPT%20Image%202025%E5%B9%B49%E6%9C%8820%E6%97%A5%20%E4%B8%8B%E5%8D%8809_47_18.png",[36,37,33],"h2",{"id":38},"php-huh-an-elephant",[17,40,41],{},"On the C battlefield, I got crushed by the pointer final boss and had to retreat. For a while afterward I basically dropped programming, only occasionally writing game scripts to feel relevant.",[17,43,44],{},"College brought me back to programming, but this time, instead of pointers, my new partner was — PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor.",[17,46,47],{},"Why did I touch programming again?",[17,49,50,51,55],{},"Because I'd chosen Information Management as my major, and one graduation requirement was ",[52,53,54],"strong",{},"\"capstone project\"",". Honestly when I first heard, the pressure was real — building a complete project independently doesn't sound easy.",[17,57,58],{},"But when I took the PHP class, I realized Web Applications were not just fun, but immediately visually rewarding — I found that especially novel.",[17,60,61],{},"There was a required Year-1 course called \"Programming Language Design\". The professor was strict, but undeniably solid. He's the one who genuinely brought me into the programming world.",[17,63,64],{},"\"Today's class is 'Web Programming'. In this class, we'll use a programming language to build a simple web application.\" He wrote PHP on the board with its full name.",[17,66,67],{},"You might think: \"College computer class — were you still gaming?\" Wrong this time. I quickly realized in college — gaming in computer class costs more than grades, potentially your future.",[17,69,70],{},"So I put games away and started actually listening — otherwise I'd fail. QQ.",[12,72,75],{"title":73,"type":74},"Note","note",[17,76,77],{},"Failing a required college course means retaking it — costs time, money, and delays graduation.",[17,79,80],{},"\"Everyone, install XAMPP — we're using Apache server to run PHP code.\" The teacher operated alongside the explanation.",[17,82,83],{},"\"XAMPP is a cross-platform web server package, including Apache, MySQL, PHP, Perl, etc.\"",[17,85,86],{},"Then: \"Also open phpDesigner 8 — an IDE specifically for editing PHP code.\"",[17,88,89],{},"For me, that was the first time using a dedicated IDE — before, I'd been using Notepad++ or plain text editors (showing my age).",[17,91,92],{},"Final demo: \"Now let's write a simple PHP program that outputs Hello, World! in the browser.\"",[94,95,100],"pre",{"className":96,"code":97,"language":98,"meta":99,"style":99},"language-php shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","\u003C?php\necho \"Hello, World!\";\n?>\n","php","",[101,102,103,116,130],"code",{"__ignoreMap":99},[104,105,108,112],"span",{"class":106,"line":107},"line",1,[104,109,111],{"class":110},"sOudu","\u003C?",[104,113,115],{"class":114},"stw71","php\n",[104,117,119,122,126],{"class":106,"line":118},2,[104,120,121],{"class":114},"echo",[104,123,125],{"class":124},"sWayO"," \"Hello, World!\"",[104,127,129],{"class":128},"s8XSl",";\n",[104,131,133],{"class":106,"line":132},3,[104,134,135],{"class":110},"?>\n",[17,137,138,139,142,143,145],{},"Honestly at that moment I didn't think it was special — I'd done C's ",[101,140,141],{},"printf",", and PHP's ",[101,144,121],{}," felt similar. But what made my eyes light up was what came next.",[17,147,148],{},"\"PHP is a server-side scripting language — embeddable in HTML, and can interact with databases.\" He explained while live-coding.",[17,150,151],{},"I sat in the back thinking:",[17,153,154],{},"\"Wait? Programs can talk to databases? That's super cool!\"",[94,156,158],{"className